main event: A strange object was spotted over Peoria, Illinois on January 12, 1958.
interesting points: The object was elliptical in shape, approximately 14 feet by 28 feet in size, with a dull aluminum appearance and no lights or trail.
The object hovered motionless at the height of electric light poles, and then departed in a westerly direction without any observed acceleration.
The object had at least 5 triangle-shaped fins and circular balls on the end of each fin.
The object was observed for about 10 minutes by multiple people in the area, including while returning home from church.
The Air Force investigated the sighting and requested information from the local police department, but there were no other reported sightings in the area.
result: Possibly a balloon, but not definitively identified.
sighted object: An elliptical-shaped object, approximately 14 feet by 28 feet, with a dull aluminum appearance and fins with circular balls on the ends.
witnesses: Multiple people, including a Mrs. J.R. Paskach and another unnamed woman
